        "content": "<p>alexcrichton <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/13141#issuecomment-4281659440\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/13141\">issue #13141</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Also ilkely related, but a SIGILL rather than a SIGSEGV:</p>\n<p><div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"cp\">$</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">cargo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">run</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">wast</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">tests</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">spec_testsuite</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">array_fill</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">wast</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">Ccollector</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"n\">null</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">Ccranelift</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">enable_heap_access_spectre_mitigation</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"kc\">false</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">Ogc</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">heap</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">may</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"k\">move</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">Ogc</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">heap</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">reservation</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">Wfunction</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">references</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"n\">gc</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">Finished</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">dev</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">profile</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">unoptimized</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">debuginfo</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">target</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mf\">0.11</span><span class=\"n\">s</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"n\">Running</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">target</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">debug</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">wasmtime</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">wast</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">tests</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">spec_testsuite</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">array_fill</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">wast</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">Ccollector</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"n\">null</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">Ccranelift</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">enable_heap_access_spectre_mitigation</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"kc\">false</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">Ogc</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">heap</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">may</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"k\">move</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">Ogc</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">heap</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">reservation</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">Wfunction</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">references</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"n\">gc</span><span class=\"err\">`</span>\n<span class=\"n\">zsh</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">illegal</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hardware</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">instruction</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">core</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">dumped</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">cargo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">run</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">wast</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">tests</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">spec_testsuite</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">array_fill</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">wast</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">Ccollector</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"n\">null</span>\n</code></pre></div><br>\n</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 587781712,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1776695388
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://github.com/alexcrichton\">alexcrichton</a> added the fuzz-bug label to <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/13141\">Issue #13141</a>.</p>",
        "id": 587817902,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1776704635
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>alexcrichton closed <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/13141\">issue #13141</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Reproduction:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"cp\">$</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">cargo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">run</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">q</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">wast</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">tests</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">spec_testsuite</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">array_fill</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">wast</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">Ogc</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">heap</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">may</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"k\">move</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">Ogc</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">heap</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">reservation</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">Wfunction</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">references</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"n\">gc</span>\n<span class=\"n\">zsh</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">segmentation</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">fault</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">cargo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">run</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">wast</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">Users</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">alex</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">code</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">wasmtime</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">tests</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">spec_testsuite</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">array_fill</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">wast</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>This first started with #13080, the introduction of GC heap tunables, due to the flags used. Unsure if it's a latent bug exposed by that or caused by that PR itself, but my guess is that PR itself.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 588712182,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1776802050
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Josef-Reichardt <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/13141#issuecomment-4333176163\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/13141\">issue #13141</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>If I understand it correctly this will fix <a href=\"https://guide.sonatype.com/vulnerability/sonatype-2026-002709\">sonatype-2026-002709</a> (High CVSS Score: 7.7), right?</p>\n<p>Any chance to get a patch release soon?</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 591298671,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1777361079
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>tschneidereit <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/13141#issuecomment-4334076995\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/13141\">issue #13141</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>@Josef-Reichardt it looks like that Sonatype CVE is about this issue, yes. However, this is not an issue the Wasmtime project would assign a CVE to; you can tell because we haven't :) The reason is that GC support isn't yet production-ready, so even if we were to publish a patch release with this fix in, we'd still strongly advise against enabling GC support in environments where you run untrusted code of any kind.</p>\n<p>As an aside, Sonatype are doing all involved a massive disservice in publishing CVEs like this: it looks like they create CVEs for issues found by OSS-Fuzz if they look security related, regardless of whether they'd be reachable in supported configurations of the project. Additionally, at least in this case the \"Components Impacted\" tab is also absolutely entirely wrong: GC support didn't exist in any way in the vast majority of releases they state are affected.</p>\n<p>Based on this, I would strongly recommend treating Sonartype as an unreliable source of information for vulnerabilities, lest you want to drown in noise.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 591329010,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1777369222
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>tschneidereit edited a <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/13141#issuecomment-4334076995\">comment</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/13141\">issue #13141</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>@Josef-Reichardt it looks like that Sonatype CVE is about this issue, yes. However, this is not an issue the Wasmtime project would assign a CVE to; you can tell because we haven't :) The reason is that GC support isn't yet production-ready, so even if we were to publish a patch release with this fix in, we'd still strongly advise against enabling GC support in environments where you run untrusted code of any kind.</p>\n<p>As an aside, Sonatype are doing all involved a massive disservice in publishing CVEs like this: it looks like they create CVEs for issues found by OSS-Fuzz if they look security related, regardless of whether they'd be reachable in supported configurations of the project. Additionally, at least in this case the \"Components Impacted\" tab is also absolutely entirely wrong: GC support didn't exist in any way in the vast majority of releases they state are affected.</p>\n<p>Based on this, I would strongly recommend treating Sonatype as an unreliable source of information for vulnerabilities, lest you want to drown in noise.</p>\n</blockquote>",
